Raw food is a cultural thing, like cuisine is a cultural thing. An uncle of mine was an amateur boxer back in the day, Golden Gloves. He ate half a pound of raw ground beef every morning as part of his breakfast when he was training hard. A surprising number of athletes and bodybuilders do that kind of thing. Raw fish is a big thing in Japan. The Inuit eat a lot of raw meat, including things like seal liver. Some anthros might have individual preferences. It's easy for me to imagine horses really liking fresh fruit and vegetables, for example.

But if we're talking about worldbuilding questions, I think you need to think in terms of what kind of setting makes sense for the story you want to tell.
